In this article, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney provides updates on various topics. He mentions that President Obama will be visiting a manufacturing facility in Iowa to discuss the role of the manufacturing sector in the American economy. Carney also addresses the impasse in the debt talks, stating that progress has been made but there are still areas of disagreement. He emphasizes that the President supports a balanced approach to reducing the deficit, which includes spending cuts and cuts in tax expenditures. Carney mentions that the next phase of the talks may involve the President and Speaker Boehner. He also briefly discusses the President's stance on gay marriage and the recent announcement regarding the Strategic Petroleum Reserve. Lastly, Carney mentions that the President is pleased with the reaction to his decision on Afghanistan and talks about refocusing on domestic needs.